cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ml_diag: Hierarchical diagnosis of ML training failures with constrained LLM arbitration"
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Milena
    family-names: Pivovarova
    affiliation: "МИЭМ НИУ ВШЭ"
    email: mapivovarova26@gmail.com
abstract: >
  A Python library for automated diagnosis and interpretation of ML training
  failures using a hierarchical cascade combined with constrained LLM
  arbitration (hard-snap), out-of-fold stacking meta-classifier, and
  split-conformal abstention layer. Six fault classes: healthy, overfitting,
  underfitting, leakage, label_noise, instability. Validated on three
  controlled fault-injection corpora (180 / 500 / 800 runs) across 8 tabular
  datasets.
keywords:
  - machine-learning
  - fault-diagnosis
  - large-language-models
  - constrained-generation
  - conformal-prediction
  - stacking
  - hierarchical-classification
